{
  "text": "Echo-guided percutaneous trans-catheter biopsy of intracardiac masses, especially in the right-sided chambers, is safe and can accurately provide histopathological diagnosis. Such an approach may therefore mitigate the need for surgical excisional biopsy and potentially alter clinical management in a large number of patients [CITATION_1] .",
